___NOTES___

NND Bot Score — server-side bot scoring for sGTM (Stape / Taggrs / any sGTM host).

WHAT IT GATES
  This variable scores the *measurement* request, not site access. Wire it as a
  blocking-trigger exception on the GA4 server tag (block when "NND Bot Score"
  is greater than your threshold) to keep bot hits out of GA4. It cannot stop a
  crawler from reading the site — that is robots.txt / WAF territory.

ROLLOUT (shadow mode first)
  1. Add the variable, run in "score" mode, send it as a GA4 event parameter
     (e.g. debug_bot_score) or watch it in Preview.
  2. Observe the distribution on real traffic for a few days.
  3. Once a threshold looks safe, add the blocking-trigger exception. A false
     positive here = a lost real conversion, so don't block on day one.

SIGNALS & WEIGHTS (see the W_* constants)
  Datacenter IP (70) is the decisive lever and is region-agnostic. Everything
  else corroborates: automation/empty UA (40); missing/forged client hints
  (25/20); platform & mobile mismatch (25/20); missing accept-language /
  accept-encoding (15/15); outdated Chromium (10); geo nudges (10). A clean
  residential browser scores 0; a residential IP must fail several integrity
  checks at once to cross 70.

IP & HEADER AVAILABILITY
  getRemoteAddress() returns the socket peer, which is your CDN/proxy if one
  fronts the container. The code reads event ip_override and the first
  X-Forwarded-For hop first to recover the real client IP. CloudFront / Global
  Accelerator ranges are intentionally NOT in the datacenter list so a visitor
  transiting them is not mistaken for a bot. IPv6 clients are not range-matched
  in v1 (they fall through to the header/UA signals).

BUNDLED RANGES
  DATACENTER_RANGES + AI_CRAWLER_RANGES are generated from the providers'
  official published lists (AWS, GCP, plus seeded Azure/DO/Hetzner/OVH/Linode/
  Vultr super-blocks; OpenAI GPTBot/ChatGPT-User/SearchBot, Googlebot and
  Google special crawlers). Refresh them periodically with build-ranges.mjs.
  Anthropic ClaudeBot and PerplexityBot publish no stable machine-readable
  range list, so they are matched by UA only (not IP-verifiable) for now.

PERMISSIONS
  Written by hand — IMPORT INTO THE GTM TEMPLATE EDITOR, run the tests, let it
  flag any permission gaps, fix in the Permissions tab, and re-export to get
  GTM's canonical permission block before deploying.
